            <div class="span9">
              <h3>Connecting It All</h3>
              <p>Next you should be able to create a CSS page and link to it in your html page. Then Javascript. WHA??? Go back to <a href="http://www.codecademy.com">codecademy</a> and go through jQuery and Javascript tracks. While your at it - why not do the Projects track to tie it all together. Also, go through <a href="http://www.codeschool.com/courses/try-jquery">Codeschool's jquery</a> and <a href="http://www.learnstreet.com/lessons/study/javascript">Learnstreet's JS</a> courses. This will take you awhile...I'll wait.</p>
              <p>Now you can appreciate <a href="http://thecodeplayer.com/">Codeplayer</a>. Woot!</p>
